In a collection of medical and other recipes at the end of the MS. of Theophilus, and which have not been written later than the commencement of the thirteenth century, I find two very·curious modes of making “azurium‚” the first of which is made from silver, and is, I confess, to me, incomprehensible, as an oxide of silver would be the result of the process instead of a blue colour. The second is from copper. I give the text for the curious.
